{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_10","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' human-intervention-logs/com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream:1.4.20/metadata-fix/codex.log\"","aggregated_output":"{\"type\":\"thread.started\",\"thread_id\":\"019ea2be-b8b5-79f0-b770-b51d4ddfa732\"}\n{\"type\":\"turn.started\"}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_0\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Using `fix-missing-reachability-metadata` because this is a metadata-gap repair for an existing library version. I’ll verify the exact GraalVM distribution first, then inspect the existing `xstream` test and metadata before reproducing the failure.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_1\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1352-202a5f49/skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_1\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1352-202a5f49/skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"---\\nname: fix-missing-reachability-metadata\\ndescription: Fix missing GraalVM reachability metadata for a specific library. Use when the user asks to fix or add metadata because required metadata is missing and tests or native-image runs fail with missing metadata errors.\\n---\\n\\n# Fix missing reachability metadata entries in the reachability-metadata.json\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nRun a reproduce-fix-verify loop for missing metadata errors. Keep running the target test until it passes with no new missing metadata entries.\\n\\nLibrary coordinates should be provided in the prompt in the format `group:artifact:version`. If you are not sure what the coordinates are, ask the user.\\n\\n## Workflow\\n\\n1. Reproduce the failure:\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` from repository root.\\n2. Capture the missing metadata from the error message:\\n   - Locate any `Missing*RegistrationError` (e.g. `MissingReflectionRegistrationError`, `MissingResourceRegistrationError`, or any other variant).\\n   - Copy the suggested JSON entry for the missing type into the corresponding section of the reachability-metadata.\\n3. Choose the target file and insert the entry:\\n   - Write to `metadata/<library-specific-metadata-directory>/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n   - Keep valid JSON and avoid duplicating an existing equivalent entry. If the type already exists but a method or field is missing, add only that method or field.\\n4. Add the missing `condition` field:\\n   - Infer it from the error stack trace.\\n   - Set the `condition` field to `{ \\\"typeReached\\\": \\\"<class>\\\" }`, where `<class>` is the first class on the stack trace whose package shares the leading namespace with the tested library's package.\\n   - Package overlap can be partial, full package equality is not required.\\n   - Example: tested library's group `org.hibernate.orm...` and the class from a stack trace `org.hibernate.resource...` is a valid match.\\n\\n5. Verify and iterate:\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` again.\\n   - If another missing entry appears, repeat from step 2.\\n   - Finish only when the test run succeeds.\\n\\n## Error Patterns\\n\\nUse this reference when deriving the missing entry and condition.\\n\\n### Missing Registration Entry Pattern\\n\\nExample error shape:\\n\\n```text\\nCaused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError:\\nCannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator()'\\n...\\nadd the following to the 'reflection' section of reachability-metadata.json:\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator\\\",\\n  \\\"methods\\\": [{ \\\"name\\\": \\\"<init>\\\", \\\"parameterTypes\\\": [] }]\\n}\\n...\\nat org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder.instantiateGeneratorViaDefaultConstructor(...)\\nat org.hibernate.resource.beans.internal.Helper$2.produceBeanInstance(...)\\n```\\n\\n### Condition Inference\\n\\nFor missing type `org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator`, a valid condition class is:\\n\\n`org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder`\\n\\nReason: both share the leading namespace `org.hibernate`, which is sufficient for this workflow.\\n\\n## Environment Troubleshooting\\n\\n- If failures look unrelated or tooling looks inconsistent, verify both `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME` point to a compatible GraalVM JDK distribution.\\n- If they are not set to GraalVM, ask the user to provide the correct GraalVM distribution path and retry.\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_2\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'env GRAALVM_HOME=/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/vj/forge/ce/sdk/latest_graalvm_home JAVA_HOME=/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/vj/forge/ce/sdk/latest_graalvm_home PATH=/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/vj/forge/ce/sdk/latest_graalvm_home/bin:$PATH native-image --version'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_2\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'env GRAALVM_HOME=/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/vj/forge/ce/sdk/latest_graalvm_home JAVA_HOME=/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/vj/forge/ce/sdk/latest_graalvm_home PATH=/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/vj/forge/ce/sdk/latest_graalvm_home/bin:$PATH native-image --version'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"native-image 25.0.3 2026-04-21\\nGraalVM Runtime Environment Oracle GraalVM 25.1.0-dev+9.1 (build 25.0.3+9-LTS-jvmci-25.1-b18)\\nSubstrate VM Oracle GraalVM 25.1.0-dev+9.1 (build 25.0.3+9-LTS, serial gc, compressed references)\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_3\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"rg --files metadata tests/src | rg 'com\\\\\\\\.thoughtworks\\\\\\\\.xstream|xstream/1\\\\\\\\.4\\\\\\\\.20'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_3\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"rg --files metadata tests/src | rg 'com\\\\\\\\.thoughtworks\\\\\\\\.xstream|xstream/1\\\\\\\\.4\\\\\\\\.20'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"metadata/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/reachability-metadata.json\\nmetadata/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/index.json\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/build.gradle\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/settings.gradle\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/SerializationMembersTest.java\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/XStreamerTest.java\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/PureJavaReflectionProviderTest.java\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/BeanProviderTest.java\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/AnnotationReflectionConverterTest.java\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/XStreamTest.java\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/gradle.properties\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/user-code-filter.json\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_4\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"The required GraalVM matches exactly, so I can use it for the whole reproduce/fix/verify loop. I’m reading the current `xstream` metadata and test setup now to see what is already covered before running the provided native trace command.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_5\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/XStreamTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_6\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,260p' metadata/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/reachability-metadata.json\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_6\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,260p' metadata/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/reachability-metadata.json\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"{}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_5\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/XStreamTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_thoughtworks_xstream.xstream;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.XStream;\\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.List;\\nimport java.util.Optional;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class XStreamTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void constructsDefaultInstanceAndRoundTripsJdkTypes() {\\n        XStream xstream = new XStream();\\n        List<Object> values = new ArrayList<>();\\n        values.add(\\\"xstream\\\");\\n        values.add(Integer.valueOf(42));\\n        values.add(LocalDate.of(2020, 2, 29));\\n        values.add(Optional.of(\\\"metadata\\\"));\\n\\n        String xml = xstream.toXML(values);\\n        Object restored = xstream.fromXML(xml);\\n\\n        assertThat(xstream.getMapper()).isNotNull();\\n        assertThat(restored).isEqualTo(values);\\n    }\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_7\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/AnnotationReflectionConverterTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_7\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/AnnotationReflectionConverterTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_thoughtworks_xstream.xstream;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.XStream;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.annotations.AnnotationProvider;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.annotations.AnnotationReflectionConverter;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.annotations.XStreamConverter;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.Converter;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.MarshallingContext;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.SingleValueConverter;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.UnmarshallingContext;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.io.HierarchicalStreamReader;\\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.io.HierarchicalStreamWriter;\\nimport java.util.Locale;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class AnnotationReflectionConverterTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void roundTripsFieldsWithLegacyAnnotationReflectionConverter() {\\n        UppercaseStringConverter.constructorInvocations = 0;\\n        UppercaseRegularValueConverter.constructorInvocations = 0;\\n        XStream xstream = configuredXStream();\\n        AnnotatedPayload payload = new AnnotatedPayload(\\\"alpha\\\", new RegularValue(\\\"beta\\\"));\\n\\n        String xml = xstream.toXML(payload);\\n        Object restored = xstream.fromXML(xml);\\n\\n        assertThat(xml).contains(\\\"<label>ALPHA</label>\\\");\\n        assertThat(xml).contains(\\\"<regularValue>BETA</regularValue>\\\");\\n        assertThat(UppercaseStringConverter.constructorInvocations).isEqualTo(1);\\n        assertThat(UppercaseRegularValueConverter.constructorInvocations).isEqualTo(1);\\n        assertThat(restored)\\n                .isInstanceOfSatisfying(AnnotatedPayload.class, value -> {\\n                    assertThat(value.label).isEqualTo(\\\"alpha\\\");\\n                    assertThat(value.regularValue.text).isEqualTo(\\\"beta\\\");\\n                });\\n    }\\n\\n    @SuppressWarnings(\\\"deprecation\\\")\\n    private static XStream configuredXStream() {\\n        XStream xstream = new XStream();\\n        xstream.alias(\\\"annotated-payload\\\", AnnotatedPayload.class);\\n        xstream.allowTypes(new Class<?>[] {AnnotatedPayload.class, RegularValue.class});\\n        AnnotationReflectionConverter converter = new AnnotationReflectionConverter(\\n                xstream.getMapper(), xstream.getReflectionProvider(), new AnnotationProvider());\\n        xstream.registerConverter(converter, XStream.PRIORITY_VERY_LOW);\\n        return xstream;\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class AnnotatedPayload {\\n        @XStreamConverter(UppercaseStringConverter.class)\\n        private String label;\\n\\n        @XStreamConverter(UppercaseRegularValueConverter.class)\\n        private RegularValue regularValue;\\n\\n        private AnnotatedPayload(String label, RegularValue regularValue) {\\n            this.label = label;\\n            this.regularValue = regularValue;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class RegularValue {\\n        private final String text;\\n\\n        private RegularValue(String text) {\\n            this.text = text;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class UppercaseStringConverter implements SingleValueConverter {\\n        private static int constructorInvocations;\\n\\n        public UppercaseStringConverter() {\\n            constructorInvocations++;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public boolean canConvert(Class type) {\\n            return String.class.equals(type);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public String toString(Object value) {\\n            return value.toString().toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Object fromString(String value) {\\n            return value.toLowerCase(Locale.ROOT);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class UppercaseRegularValueConverter implements Converter {\\n        private static int constructorInvocations;\\n\\n        public UppercaseRegularValueConverter() {\\n            constructorInvocations++;\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public boolean canConvert(Class type) {\\n            return RegularValue.class.equals(type);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public void marshal(Object source, HierarchicalStreamWriter writer, MarshallingContext context) {\\n            RegularValue value = (RegularValue) source;\\n            writer.setValue(value.text.toUpperCase(Locale.ROOT));\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Object unmarshal(HierarchicalStreamReader reader, UnmarshallingContext context) {\\n            return new RegularValue(reader.getValue().toLowerCase(Locale.ROOT));\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_8\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'git status --short'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_8\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'git status --short'\",\"aggregated_output\":\" M tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/user-code-filter.json\\n?? metadata/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"There are already local changes under the same `xstream` fixture: `user-code-filter.json` is modified and the metadata directory is currently untracked. I’m checking whether those are the current scaffold I should build on, then I’ll run the exact reproduction command against them rather than overwrite blindly.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_10\",\"type\":\"todo_list\",\"items\":[{\"text\":\"Inspect current xstream fixture files and local changes to understand baseline metadata state\",\"completed\":false},{\"text\":\"Reproduce the native-image metadata failure with the exact GraalVM and provided command\",\"completed\":false},{\"text\":\"Update reachability metadata to cover the missing registrations without duplicating existing entries\",\"completed\":false},{\"text\":\"Verify with the same GraalVM using the failing command and targeted Gradle checks\",\"completed\":false}]}