ective. So, I’m wondering if I need to ensure we have clean, untracked metadata to address this situation better. It's crucial to clarify these points for effective instrumentation moving forward.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering metadata management**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about how to handle metadata. It contains \\\\\\\"{}\\\\\\\" and if it's generated externally, maybe it doesn't need to be part of our artifact. But we didn't create it, and the user might expect changes. Should I mention untracked metadata left untouched? There's this rule about never modifying reachability metadata, so removing it might be risky. I should inspect whether PureJavaReflectionProviderTest is tracked using `git ls-files`. That could help clarify the situation.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_4lOZmpXd2bUgmqlOzJSLpMEL|fc_045a421a425e7438016a25847006d48196b07661e3f969b891\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git ls-files tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/PureJavaReflectionProviderTest.java tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/build.gradle\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1264, \"output\": 1207, \"cacheRead\": 82432, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 84903, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1780843601626, \"responseId\": \"resp_045a421a425e7438016a2584525aa481968aad88bfc5be1252\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_4lOZmpXd2bUgmqlOzJSLpMEL|fc_045a421a425e7438016a25847006d48196b07661e3f969b891\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/build.gradle\\ntests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/PureJavaReflectionProviderTest.java\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1780843632429}]}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_start\"}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 0, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1780843632432}}\n[assistant-event] thinking_start\n[assistant-event] thinking_end\n[assistant-event] text_start\n[assistant] I investigated the remaining two call sites:\n[assistant] \n[assistant] - `ObjectStreamClass.lookup(type)` at line 134\n[assistant] - `ObjectInputStream.readObject()` at line 148\n[assistant] \n[assistant] They are only reached in `PureJavaReflectionProvider.instantiateUsingSerialization(...)` when:\n[assistant] \n[assistant] ```java\n[assistant] if (Reflections.newInstance != null) {\n[assistant]     ...\n[assistant]     return Reflections.newInstance.invoke(osClass, new Object[0]);\n[assistant] }\n[assistant] ```\n[assistant] \n[assistant] is skipped, meaning `PureJavaReflectionProvider.Reflections.newInstance` must be `null`.\n[assistant] \n[assistant] For XStream `1.4.20` on the current JDK, that field becomes `null` only if XStream cannot make the private JDK method `ObjectStreamClass.newInstance()` accessible. The supported historical way to force that was a `SecurityManager` denying `ReflectPermission(\"suppressAccessChecks\")`, but the current test JDK rejects `System.setSecurityManager(...)` with:\n[assistant] \n[assistant] ```text\n[assistant] UnsupportedOperationException: Setting a Security Manager is not supported\n[assistant] ```\n[assistant] \n[assistant] Removing `--add-opens` is not a supported alternative: it causes module-access failure during XStream’s internal static initialization rather than exercising the fallback path as normal library behavior.\n[assistant] \n[assistant] So I left those two call sites uncovered rather than adding an unstable or unsupported test path. The failing `SecurityManager`-based fallback test has been removed/reverted, leaving only the supported `PureJavaReflectionProvider` coverage that already passed and covered the five reachable call sites.\n[assistant-event] text_end\n[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_045a421a425e7438016a258471ff448196a2d7a866678e22bc\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqJYR88GiuXX6vmL9dlfV1B-AVoHJMPR4164QAgaBgysC1U2ta1JiMoIWH_s3dcmSfMqnmZ7DD3SzOULNYsGk0ddME2Wq_X1ZgYe8IBYNvsgasyW4UNjIZTvWTc2-705YdIbqZjoEMVTzhsK7t-SipqoGP6xla312gBQbCdEAXQNfsSwyOMtNPsDHl0YKx7C0eT0eeOVi0nXtkZ7yOwaERwMP0uIQbe07rSGRjU_Xa-DMgL7YdyC4I4WEvdF8j4ohjhWdlXy99gGYmIrcdSK3LDJhmb48AdGFtZl7OZHqtN_FLtecZrLKV2aAlrJ0lhcuaqxyj7Wb20LaBkVxqWGvAob__7cqkNyS4kByMXFohAJGGpCQl2Im8kluFNeVgZVRXfZ9NetfLTj1LeUqLMTuaDX5XyDvj9s9SH58jnKwa1-raEBCVKdJ0kK-BjAyTN1geTm6figM11ta4b-pPSH-dvScjAe5srERRh9NjXnuPPi2lePpvsj4fwxm2ovI4E3C7v5QT_Qnpr-rJDe4to79foOi5VMP1RRax0JoSIsJ058JpiwGpQgXWCKySXlTXnHcIU1ghNzfVOUpRNt3tjIIY0S4A6d3k-bHJVYtvbDl2XB6qBCz9YhU7HbS4SG17O2dq6-eYH4cJB-fOc_LBv0xYwTjh7cUtBuf5yxCPRrALaeY_x97gzrYB672kigpS7fKXdyOXl2wL4BbjaFtahC--X3zVzvo1Q0Rx4kdSCJ6xHpK4OcxXpn9UtU3yp8t7lvhHIgolRW8vYrkKsNwH25ZvMGDYCSbB9_c7rbij5_Lm94CRLUTtT8OBj6Y8Tyk_tVRq88GJh-MVRfE7UMqPsg_OfLXMRo6NsU2y51Eep1S54UZFps-HcDhkDyKEmbGCq109p7o_64Yo-WLa5Uvb7vElvc6Ki0tRrp0Mod3eFGG8aOG58eGnIv_csre5YSDjqYMcsQony73ogjN70-JBeYa200NtXCun4ZHjxh1KbUpIogd4CyTmWO_x3_nfyH4lgRc4lQSYn6tzdWyQ7CComoFELDj0ZaRobEYeZtMOL1H98FEAJmpLEmENKITFvFJ3o7h6xjIpU7cZ9vZVMGTcKsOmUyWW4MJUt4G0IUcAU697vLTh3kh46iD1suCCi_RguBWyPZ1Whhj7H0MsciW-njNpPPm6h_lbvDOIHSVvUwoPhQAj2W3t94Ttp9618aVL1Hc_9JEdd6bsa40Su8qmSQmIBlbVeave1e_YmLeY4N1yS7Yuuim_K12