hould clarify if it’s a concern for dynamic reflection metadata generation for native images too.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Investigating fromXML issues**\\\\n\\\\nI see that the agent is using `outer` with fromXML on the JVM via reflection to instantiate StringOnlyConverterLookup and its fields, which generates metadata. However, there's an issue with active call sites, especially the Class#forName at line 54, where the class might be synthetic. Our custom XStream constructor still needs class initialization. I think I should ensure that fromXML with default permissions includes the top-level helper for ConverterLookup. It's important to get this finalized!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Updated `XStreamerTest` to avoid embedding a full default `XStream` configuration, which was pulling in default converter internals like `DurationConverter` and requiring more JDK module opens.\\n\\nChanges made:\\n\\n- `tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/XStreamerTest.java`\\n  - Uses a minimal `XStream` instance with a custom `ConverterLookup` that supports only `String`/`null`.\\n  - Still exercises:\\n    - `XStreamer.toXML(...)`\\n    - `XStreamer.fromXML(...)`\\n    - embedded `XStream` configuration round-trip\\n  - Avoids serializing the default converter registry that caused access failures for `javax.xml.datatype.DatatypeFactory`.\\n\\nThe existing `java.util` open remains in `build.gradle` because serializing the embedded `XStream` object can still traverse internal synchronized JDK collections.\\n\\nI did not run the Gradle test command locally, per instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_034cbbecb2ce62c8016a2587a5fb2c81958aa9ce2f1e29d0f1\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2237, \"output\": 725, \"cacheRead\": 61952, \"cac