ation isn't active in the child process, it seems ineffective. So, I’m wondering if I need to ensure we have clean, untracked metadata to address this situation better. It's crucial to clarify these points for effective instrumentation moving forward.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering metadata management**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about how to handle metadata. It contains \\\\\\\"{}\\\\\\\" and if it's generated externally, maybe it doesn't need to be part of our artifact. But we didn't create it, and the user might expect changes. Should I mention untracked metadata left untouched? There's this rule about never modifying reachability metadata, so removing it might be risky. I should inspect whether PureJavaReflectionProviderTest is tracked using `git ls-files`. That could help clarify the situation.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_4lOZmpXd2bUgmqlOzJSLpMEL|fc_045a421a425e7438016a25847006d48196b07661e3f969b891\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git ls-files tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/PureJavaReflectionProviderTest.java tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/build.gradle\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1264, \"output\": 1207, \"cacheRead\": 82432, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 84903, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1780843601626, \"responseId\": \"resp_045a421a425e7438016a2584525aa481968aad88bfc5be1252\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream:1.4.20/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-07T14-36-02-921114Z.log:7231:[tool-exec] start id=call_4lOZmpXd2bUgmqlOzJSLpMEL|fc_045a421a425e7438016a25847006d48196b07661e3f969b891 name=bash args={\"command\": \"git ls-files tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream